<TITLE> Two foreigners killed in raid on Afghan police centre </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Afganistan, June 07 (bdnews24.com/REUTERS) - Two foreign nationals were killed in a suicide bomb and commando attack on an Afghan police training centre in Kandahar on Monday, officials said. An American and another unidentifed foreigner, both with the U.S. security firm DynCorp, which is contracted to help with police training, were killed in the attack. The Kandahar governor's spokesman said one suspected Taliban insurgent blew himself up, blasting open the gates of the training centre and allowing two other insurgents to enter and start a gunfight before they were killed. The Taliban insurgency is at its height since the hardline Islamist group were overthrown in a U.S.-led invasion in 2001. U.S.-led NATO forces are planning an offensive on Kandahar and its environs in the coming months, mixing a troop surge with governance and development project
